Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{=16}===============================DIALOGUE============================
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.86,0:00:05.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,So Robin's in that building behind you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.65,0:00:08.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Get out of my way, bull guy! - OG}{Get outta my way, bull guy! - Z}Get outta my way, bull!{arch: for accuracy and consistency with EL04 23:32}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.40,0:00:17.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It seems that you guys haven't noticed... that what you're doing is a world-class crime. - OG}{\q2}It seems you are all incredibly unaware\Nthat you're committing a major world-class crime.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.37,0:02:18.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Bring down every single one of them here! - OG}Take them all down right here!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.45,0:02:21.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Fire! Send the Marines packing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.88,0:02:31.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You... bastards! - OG}You damn bastards!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:44.02,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I understand! - OG}{I'll tell them! - Z}I see!{arch: The line is pretty generic but I'd still go for something like this}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.02,0:02:48.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So, when the brothers Sodom\Nand Gomorrah were going to die - OG}So, back when the brothers were\Nat death's door in a sea king's stomach,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:54.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{in a sea king's stomach, the Franky Family\Nsaved them and said this to them... - OG}the Franky Family saved\NSodom and Gomorrah and told them,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.07,0:02:57.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're full, so we're not gonna eat you guys! - OG}"We're full, so we're not gonna eat you."{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.45,0:03:02.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since then, they have been loyal\Nto Franky, who saved their lives. - OG}{Since then, they've been dutiful and loyal\Nto their savior Franky. - Z}Since then, they've been\Nloyal to their savior Franky.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.58,0:03:05.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Well, - OG}Let me guess.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.75,0:03:11.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{they just happened to be in the stomach of a sea king that the Franky Family was eating, right? - OG}The Franky Family was eating the sea king\Nwho had swallowed these two, right?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:14.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.51,0:03:16.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.34,0:03:19.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But can you watch where you're going?\NYou're making me nervous. - OG}{Can you at least watch where you're going?\NYou're making me nervous. - Z}Can you watch where you're going?\NYou're making me nervous.{Gab, CPS}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.35,0:03:25.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He says, "I'll be faithful to Big Bro Franky\Nfor the rest of my life!"- OG}He says, "I'll follow Big Bro Franky\Nfor the rest of my life!"{PP}{Shows up as a flashback in EL23 @05:34}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.44,0:03:29.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He must be really happy that\Nsomeone understands his language. - OG}He looks overjoyed to finally meet someone\Nwho understands what he says.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.07,0:03:43.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{He's asking: "By the way, was it okay that the guy with the mask didn't get on with you guys?" - OG}He asked, "By the way, is it okay\Nthat the masked guy didn't hop on with you?"{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.58,0:03:44.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.37,0:03:49.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.54,0:03:52.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I-I don't see Sogeking onboard! - OG}S-Sogeking isn't on board!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:56.76,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1366.4,795.4)}Why?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.88,0:03:59.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\pos(572.8,617.8)}Did he fall off?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.14,0:04:02.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\pos(948.8,633.8)}{No... Come to think of it,\Nhe wasn't riding with us from the start! - OG}No... Come to think of it,\Nhe never got on from the start!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.14,0:04:04.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't tell me he ran...! - OG}Don't tell me he ran away.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.77,0:04:13.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.69,0:04:16.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Stop blocking the path!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.86,0:04:19.95,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you want to go through us, beat me first! - OG}If you wish to continue, defeat me first!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.95,0:04:20.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Get out...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.62,0:04:23.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,of our way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.83,0:04:29.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's not gonna be that easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.21,0:04:32.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Battleship Cannon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.42,0:04:40.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Dammit! There's only\Nthree of them! Do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.35,0:04:46.93,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,You seem like a strong fighter.{W7 09 - 33:19}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:50.02,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Can you beat them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.02,0:04:51.19,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Yes, I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.48,0:04:59.20,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,People waver when faced with uncertainty.{W7 14 - 22:59}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.91,0:05:06.12,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Once they know she needs help,\Nthey won't stop until she's safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.75,0:05:10.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That guy will... definitely...! - OG}If anyone can do it... it's that guy!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.50,0:05:14.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Bring down that rope guy! - OG}Take out the one with the rope!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.54,0:05:16.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Not gonna happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.80,0:05:21.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Shrouds and Ratline Knot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.01,0:05:23.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh, shoot! - OG}Oh, crap!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.10,0:05:25.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You've reached a dead end. - OG}End of the line.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.97,0:05:27.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.11,0:05:37.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why don't you tell me your point? - OG}What's your point?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.28,0:05:44.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The World Government is a huge,\Npowerful organization - OG}The World Government is\Nan expansive and powerful organization{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.24,0:05:48.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{that is comprised of over 170\Ncountries around the world. - OG}comprised of over 170 nations\Nacross the globe.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:51.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Invading this island, which\Nbelongs to the government... - OG}Assaulting this government-owned island{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.08,0:05:55.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{is an act of rebellion against all those countries! - OG}amounts to an act of rebellion\Nagainst every one of these countries!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.84,0:06:01.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Upon their dignity, the government will\Nexpose all of you to public ridicule... - OG}To preserve its dignity, the government\Nwill submit each of you to public ridicule{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.47,0:06:04.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{and will bestow a merciless death upon you. - OG}and grant you all a grisly death.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.22,0:06:06.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Your group is composed of a meager few dozen. - OG}You brought with you a mere few dozen.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.56,0:06:10.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That is nowhere near enough. - OG}You are woefully outnumbered.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.18,0:06:14.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All I did... was tell you to get outta my way! - OG}All I said... was to get outta my way!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.19,0:06:16.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{My point is that you, - OG}{\q2}My "point" is that you all have no future.{Z - This refers back to Luffy's question at 05:57}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.40,0:06:22.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{My point is that you, who entered the gates \Nof Enies Lobby, have no future... even if I do move out of your way. That's all. - OG}Even if I were to move, you have\Nalready entered the gates of Enies Lobby.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.82,0:06:24.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Fighting is pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.45,0:06:29.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm pretty sure you got a good taste of our\NSix Powers at Galley-La's mansion... - OG}You have seen our Six Powers firsthand\Nat Galley-La's mansion,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.62,0:06:33.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{as well as the difference in\Nour levels of fighting ability. - OG}and you know your fighting prowess\Npales in comparison.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:38.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.38,0:06:40.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,but for some reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.50,0:06:43.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't feel\Nlike I'm gonna lose at all now! - OG}losing just doesn't feel possible right now!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:48.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Gum-Gum...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.31,0:06:50.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Iron Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.81,0:06:52.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}...Rifle!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.15,0:07:05.91,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.91,0:07:10.99,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,I don't remember him being this powerful\Nwhen I fought him at the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:14.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Gatling!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.16,0:07:15.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Shave!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.73,0:07:47.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The world[/i1]this[/i0]... the government[/i1]that[/i0]... - OG}World this... Government that...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.20,0:07:49.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't care about that stuff. - OG}{You can all do whatever you want. - arch - lit: "Do whatever you want with that", i.e. probably adressing Blueno. The OG line is a bit too on the nose for me; Luffy usually doesn't say outright that he doesn't care - he doesn't even think about it, so him not caring wouldn't be a conscious decision.}Do whatever you want with that.{PP - I like "Do whatever you want with that" more, since he is refering to doing whatever with the government and countries, not doing whatever in general.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.00,0:07:58.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We just came here... to take Robin back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:09.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wh-Wh-What're we gonna do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.35,0:08:13.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In any case, - OG}At this point...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.06,0:08:17.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{we don't have the option\Nof going back to get him at this point. - OG}going back and getting him\Nis no longer an option.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.02,0:08:21.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he'll work things out on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.23,0:08:23.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But there are guards everywhere on this island. - OG}But the island's swarming with guards!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.28,0:08:27.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,He isn't Luffy. If he's\Nby himself, his life will be–
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.07,0:08:33.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{After surmounting each island,\Nwe got stronger without realizing it. - OG}Even if we don't realize it, every one of us\Ngrows stronger with each challenge we face.{arch: The japanese stresses "unknowingly" and explicitly mentions "islands" twice. I put the latter in the following line, but the former should be included here if possible.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:37.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That guy always survived life-or-death\Nsituations on every island. - OG}That guy has faced life-or-death situations\Non every island we've been to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.04,0:08:41.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No one in our group would die so easily. - OG}No one on our crew would die so easily.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.13,0:08:49.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Look! We're almost to the courthouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.89,0:08:53.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Bring them down at all costs!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.56,0:09:02.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Oh, crap! King bull! - OG}Oh, crap! The king bull!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.48,0:09:05.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All right! We brought down one of them! - OG }All right! We took one of 'em down!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.19,0:09:07.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Sodom!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.20,0:09:14.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Sodom! This is bad! I have to treat him right away! - OG}Sodom! This is bad!\NHe needs immediate treatment!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.74,0:09:18.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Sodom! Stand firm! Don't fall yet! - OG}Sodom! Stand tall! Don't fall yet!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.66,0:09:21.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Guys! Move over right away! - OG}You guys gotta jump over right now!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.79,0:09:25.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hurry it up! Sodom can't go on much longer! - OG}Get the lead out! Sodom is finished!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.67,0:09:30.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That trench mortar hit him in the chest! - OG}That shell hit 'im square in the chest!{Z}{This shows up as a flashback later in EL23 @05:48}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.05,0:09:31.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Get over here before he falls! - OG}Hurry, before he falls!{Z}{This shows up as a flashback later in EL23 @05:51}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.01,0:09:35.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No one's getting saved\Nunless you guys keep moving!{This shows up as a flashback later in EL23 @05:52}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.44,0:09:49.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,He said, "Go!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.46,0:10:05.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's coming down!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.56,0:10:27.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No one's riding it! - OG}No one's on board!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.52,0:10:29.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.53,0:10:31.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hey... - OG}Come on...{arch: With the intonation it doesn't really work as a full sentence, so something like "Stop staring and get going already".}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.90,0:10:34.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Gomorrah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.83,0:10:46.58,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,I wasn't able to get on the king bull.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.58,0:10:49.46,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{What am I gonna do? I'm way behind now. - OG}What do I do? I'm way behind now.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:54.09,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{In any case, those shipwrights are amazing! - OG}But wow, those shipwrights are amazing!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:57.72,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Anyway, I left the group. - OG}Anyway, I'm already off the crew.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.72,0:11:00.39,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Should I just run? - OG}Should I just run?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.81,0:11:09.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,N-N-No! Running is the last thing I'll do!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.48,0:11:14.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm Usopp! I'm a man! I went so far\Nas to hide my identity to follow them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.32,0:11:18.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're facing a crisis where Robin is\Nsacrificing herself to protect all of us! - OG}Robin's risking her life to protect us,\Nand the situation's dire!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:20.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I have to do it at all costs! - OG}I will persevere to the end!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:22.20,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,All right...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.20,0:11:24.58,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{There's only one\Nway to get to everyone. - OG}There's only one way to catch up to everyone!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.87,0:11:32.34,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'll carry out Operation: Disguise Myself\Nas One of the Government Workers... - OG}{\q2}Operation: Disguise Myself as a Government Agent\Nand Pass by Them Unnoticed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.05,0:11:35.63,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah, that'd be good. - OG}Yes, very good.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.51,0:11:37.64,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Yeah, that'd be good. - OG}I'll...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.64,0:11:38.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.14,0:11:43.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Whoa! What?! What?!\NAre they trying to drown me?! - OG}What?! What?! Some kind\Nof watery ambush?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.27,0:11:45.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Enemy attack! Enemy attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.77,0:11:48.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{How regrettable! - OG}Oh, the shame!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.90,0:11:53.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The giant woke up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.90,0:11:56.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We screwed up in our fiftieth year!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.65,0:11:59.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I'm sorry, Bosses! - OG}Oimo's sorry, Chiefs!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:11:59.91,Secondary-207+,,0,0,0,,{Bosses? - OG}Chiefs?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:04.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We are a disgrace to Elbaph!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.04,0:12:06.96,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,E-Elbaph?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.96,0:12:11.04,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Elbaph... Bosses... - OG}Elbaph... Chiefs...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.63,0:12:12.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't tell me... - OG}Just a moment!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.67,0:12:16.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I-Is it possible that you're from Elbaph, the warriors' island?! - OG}I-Is it possible that you're from Elbaph,\Nthe island of warriors?!{Zenef: "island of warriors" isn't in the writing guide}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.97,0:12:18.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.97,0:12:22.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I-I-I am Sogeking from Sniper Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.14,0:12:25.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Can you explain what you're talking about? - OG}C-Can you elaborate on what you just said?{PP}{Referring back to Oimo crying about his chiefs}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.73,0:12:28.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.48,0:12:32.48,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's pointless to tell you about it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.40,0:12:39.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Oimo and Kashi were pirates\Nup until 100 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.82,0:12:42.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We ran amok all over the world. - OG}We ran wild all over the world.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.70,0:12:45.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But one day on a certain island...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.87,0:12:49.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Our two bosses then started to duel. - OG}{Then our two bosses began to duel. - Z}{Then our two chiefs began\Nto battle one another. - Z}Our two chiefs began to battle one another.{Gab, flashback to LG is no longer between these lines}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.04,0:12:55.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The group was split up, and everyone ended up going back to their hometown. - OG}The crew split apart, and everyone\Nended up returning to their homeland.{PP/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.71,0:12:58.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It was a life-or-death battle between warriors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.22,0:13:01.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{At the very least, the winner was\Nsupposed to come back to the island. - OG}We expected the winner\Nto at least come back to the island;{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.97,0:13:05.72,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but even after several decades,\Nneither of them came back. - OG}however, several decades passed,\Nand neither one returned.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.72,0:13:10.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{After 50 years passed, me and Kashi\Nthought something was wrong, - OG}It was fifty years later when Oimo and Kashi\Nthought something might've gone wrong,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.73,0:13:13.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{so we set out to sea to go get those two. - OG}so we set out to sea to bring them home.{PP/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:17.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But on our way, we got caught by the Marines,\Nand they made us tell them everything. - OG}But we got caught by the Marines,\Nand they made us tell them everything.{Zenef: IMO, "on our way" is implied, so we can safely shorten this line to fit the VA}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.82,0:13:21.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Then, in return, we were told a shocking story. - OG}In return, they told us a shocking story.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:28.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They said that our bosses, who were very strong,\Nwere confined in the government's great prison. - OG}They said that our two mighty chiefs were\Nbeing held in the government's huge prison!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.62,0:13:29.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.71,0:13:32.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That was about fifty years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.04,0:13:36.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The government gave us these conditions:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.75,0:13:40.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If me and Kashi worked for\Nthe government for 100 years... - OG}If Oimo and Kashi served\Nthe government for 100 years—{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.88,0:13:45.55,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{in other words, if we could protect this\Ngate on Enies Lobby for 100 years... - OG}that is, if we could protect this gate\Non Enies Lobby for an entire century—{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.55,0:13:51.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{they'd release the chiefs\Nand let us all go home to Elbaph. - OG}they'd release the chiefs\Nand let us all go home to Elbaph.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.19,0:13:55.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since a giant's life span is 300 years,\Nwe thought 100 years was nothing. - OG}Since giants live for 300 years,\Nwe figured 100 years wouldn't be so bad.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.65,0:13:59.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So we accepted the conditions and\Nhave kept fighting for the past 50 years. - OG}So we accepted and kept fighting\Nthese past fifty years.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.11,0:14:03.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{But the gate was broken open today by pirates! - OG}But today, pirates came\Nand broke open the gate!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.28,0:14:05.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{To think something like this happened! - OG}I never imagined this would happen!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.66,0:14:07.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:10.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The chiefs will now be\Nimprisoned for the rest of their lives! - OG}The chiefs will be kept in prison\Ntill their dying breaths!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.04,0:14:13.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey! H-H-Hold on a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:15.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{There's something funny about that story. - OG}{You know, funny story, but– -Z}That's funny–{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.67,0:14:17.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's "funny" about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.42,0:14:20.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,If you're gonna laugh at our pride, then–
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:23.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No, no, I didn't mean it that way!\NI meant that it's weird! - OG}No, no! I don't mean funny-ha-ha,\NI meant funny-weird!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.93,0:14:25.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Weird, you say?! - OG}Now you think it's "weird"?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.47,0:14:30.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Because during our journey before\Nwe came here, we met them! - OG}Listen! During our journey here,\Nwe actually met those two!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.19,0:14:37.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The two you've been talking about,\Nthe Elbaph warriors, Dorry and Brogy... - OG}The two you've been talking about—\Nthe warriors of Elbaph, Dorry and Brogy—{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.94,0:14:43.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,have been fighting an evenly matched duel\Non that island for the past 100 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.70,0:14:50.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What?! How come you know their names?! - OG}Wha...?! How... do you know their names?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:52.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What?! That's impossible! - OG}No, that's impossible!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.00,0:14:55.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If you wanna hear more proof,\NI'll tell you as much as you want! - OG}You want more proof? Well, I've got it!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:03.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And... - OG}Like so...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.23,0:15:18.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You still don't believe me?! What do I have\Nto tell you to get you to believe me?! - OG}Don't believe me?!\NWhat else do you wanna know?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.65,0:15:25.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,About their weapons?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.49,0:15:30.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Their techniques?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.62,0:15:34.08,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,That's 73,466 duels...{LG 02 - 06:31}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.08,0:15:35.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I know everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.75,0:15:39.46,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,...and 73,466 draws.{LG 02 - 06:35}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:45.13,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We really met them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.72,0:15:54.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's a big fat lie that they\Ngot caught 50 years ago! - OG}They got caught fifty years ago?!\NYou were told a whopper of a lie!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.41,0:16:20.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It's coming! Take aim!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.29,0:16:23.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Let it get closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.63,0:16:26.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's a trench mortar!\NDodge it, Gomorrah! - OG}That's artillery fire! Dodge it, Gomorrah!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.76,0:16:33.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This center path isn't good.\NThey're fully prepared and waiting in ambush! - OG}This central path is no good!\NThey're all set up to ambush us!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.89,0:16:35.22,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We're gonna go a different way! - OG}We've gotta take a detour!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:44.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You won't get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.20,0:16:49.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Sodom...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.74,0:16:51.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.13,0:17:06.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Chopper...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.13,0:17:10.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hm?! The mobile transponder snail is ringing?! - OG}Huh? The baby transponder snail?!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.76,0:17:12.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hello? Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.47,0:17:14.68,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's me. - OG}It's us.{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.68,0:17:15.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{That's old lady Kokoro!}Old lady Kokoro!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.85,0:17:17.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{What're you calling for? - OG}Why're you calling...?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.60,0:17:20.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Sounds like you guys are still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.60,0:17:22.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{There's something I forgot to tell you. - OG}Good, 'cause I forgot to tell you something.{PP/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.81,0:17:26.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{I'm sure you guys are busy,\Nso I'll make it quick. Listen carefully. - OG}I know you're all busy,\Nso I'll be quick. Listen up.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.44,0:17:32.24,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{On the map drawn by Paulie, there's no path from the courthouse to the Gates of Justice, right? -OG}{Viz doesn't say "Gates of Justice" here, but instead says "Tower of Law". Our writing guide has this as "Tower of Justice". Same goes for the line @17:45}On Paulie's map, you won't see a path\Nfrom the courthouse to the Tower of Justice.{arch: yup}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.57,0:17:35.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's right. I was just thinking about that. - OG}She's right. I wondered about that.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.53,0:17:39.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{Look at the courthouse.\NThere's a tower on each side, right? - OG}Look at the courthouse.\NThere's a tower on either side, right?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.54,0:17:40.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah, there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:45.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's a lever on the top floor of each tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.67,0:17:50.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{When you pull them,\Na drawbridge will come down from the courthouse to the Gates of Justice. - OG}{Same note as @17:27}When you pull both, a drawbridge lowers\Nfrom the courthouse to the Tower of Justice.{arch: yup yup}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.92,0:17:53.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Lady, how come you know that stuff? - OG}How in the heck do you know all that?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:57.47,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I came here with Tom{-san}\Nto fix the bridge a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.47,0:17:59.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{That damn, stupid government! - OG}That ungrateful, idiot-run government!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.89,0:18:01.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Don't take it out on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.89,0:18:03.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chimney wants to talk to you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.98,0:18:07.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hello, pirate lady! Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.11,0:18:09.07,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Whoa! What is it, Chimney?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.07,0:18:15.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{Listen. I saw the rubber pirate guy\Non the rooftop of the courthouse. - OG}So, I saw the rubber pirate guy\Non the rooftop of the courthouse.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.83,0:18:18.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Really?! Luffy was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.70,0:18:23.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{I saw rocks collapsing there, too,\Nso it looks like he's going on a rampage. - OG}I saw rubble collapsing there, too,\Nso it looks like he's really letting loose.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.25,0:18:25.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,On the rooftop?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:27.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Got it. Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.34,0:18:33.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{Pirate girl, keep the transponder snail\Nconnected so that I'll know what's going on over there. - OG}Pirate girl, keep the transponder snail\Nconnected so that I can stay in the know.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.26,0:18:34.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Okay... - OG}Roger!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.09,0:18:35.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{So they said. - OG}{And now... - Z}So...{arch: very similar to Zen's but fits a bit better to the Japanese}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.18,0:18:38.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{And now we know where we have to go. - OG}{And now we know where to go. - Z}So now we know where to go.{arch: see previous line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:40.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Yeah!\N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:47.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Alright, you guys go straight\Nto the courthouse and meet up with Straw Hat{-san}.{Flashback for Enies Lobby 23 @timestamp 04:35}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.11,0:18:48.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.24,0:18:56.62,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We're gonna split into two groups\Nand bring down that drawbridge.{Will be a flashback in EL23@04:42}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.08,0:19:00.99,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Take us to the courthouse, Gomorrah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.38,0:19:11.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Gomorrah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:21.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Dammit! Who are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.03,0:19:37.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,It won't be that easy... you damn trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.91,0:19:45.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,All right! The second one is down too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.04,0:19:49.42,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The pirates no longer have\Na way of getting around! - OG}We've stopped the pirates dead in their tracks!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.42,0:19:51.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Surround them and bring them down! - OG}Surround them and take them out!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.17,0:19:53.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{To all the guards in Enies Lobby! - OG}Calling all Enies Lobby troops!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.88,0:19:59.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{At the center of Block D in the southeast area,\Nwe brought down the king bull\Nthat the pirates were riding on! - OG}{\q2}At the center of Block D in the southeast,\Nwe brought down the king bull the pirates were riding!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.51,0:20:03.89,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{Call in all the soldiers\Nand fully blockade Block D! - OG}This is a call to all troops\Nto regroup and seal off Block D!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.35,0:20:05.27,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I repeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.27,0:20:08.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{All guards, fully blockade Block D! - OG}All troops, regroup and seal off Block D!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:11.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Looks like the jury delivered the verdict.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.57,0:20:15.03,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,No one can beat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.49,0:20:18.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Why won't you speak? - OG}{Go and say something! - arch}– Just say something!\N– Just say something!{Z- better mouthfeel on this variation}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.74,0:20:19.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Yes, sir!\N– Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.70,0:20:21.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,We'll capture them right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.79,0:20:30.17,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,The guards that we passed\Nare catching up. This isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.79,0:20:33.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{More and more are coming\Nfrom the front and the sides. - OG}They're piling in from\Nthe front and the sides too.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.88,0:20:35.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{The trench mortars are aiming at us, too. - OG}And the artillery's aimed right at us!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.01,0:20:39.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,This is terrible! There are thousands of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.34,0:20:45.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,If we get surrounded by them\Nin a place like this, we'll be goners!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.69,0:20:51.44,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're a lucky person. - OG}You're one lucky lady.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.44,0:20:53.77,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Most people don't get\Na rescue squad, y'know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.23,0:21:00.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Well, it's not like I'm jealous\Nthat my underlings aren't here to rescue me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.72,0:21:20.88,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.88,0:21:22.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I forgot about something. - OG}I almost forgot.{Not exactly a Flashback, but it kind of refers to Spandam's line in EL03 @07:15. The VA says something different in both places, so there's no real need to match the lines.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.64,0:21:24.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Take these with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:31.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wait! Aren't those devil fruits?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.19,0:21:38.57,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is that... - OG}Could it be...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.57,0:21:43.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{true?! - OG}truly true?!{Zenef: Gotta spice up Kumadori's speech. The JP VA really hams it up here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.16,0:21:46.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I've never seen them before! - OG}I've never seen one before!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.33,0:21:49.58,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Me neither! - OG}The same goes for me!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.58,0:21:51.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is bad!\NKeep those away from me! - OG}Not good! Keep those away from me!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.54,0:21:55.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{What's the big fuss, Jabra? - OG}What's all this hullabaloo, Jabra?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.38,0:21:57.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You nutbag! Don't you know? - OG}You idiot! Don't you know?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.50,0:22:03.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Those with devil fruit powers have a devil \Ndwelling inside their bodies! - OG}Those with devil fruit powers have\Nan actual devil dwelling inside their bodies!{Evo: slight rephrasing to make the repetition of devil not so jarring}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.09,0:22:05.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{For example,\Nif I get close to a fruit, - OG}{For example,\Nif I get close to that fruit, - Z}That means, if I get close to that fruit,{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.80,0:22:13.35,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{a devil will jump out and start fighting\Nthe devil in me, causing my body to explode! - OG}its devil will jump out and start fighting\Nthe devil in me, causing my body to explode!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.94,0:22:15.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Is that true? - OG}You pulling my leg?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.69,0:22:18.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,How foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.82,0:22:23.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It takes a sloppy intelligence agent\Nto be misled by a rumor. - OG}Only a sloppy intelligence agent\Nwould be misled by a rumor.{TMM}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.36,0:22:29.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Grand Line scientists have already discovered\Nhow the fruits transfer their powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.83,0:22:34.54,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You're talking about when someone eats two fruits. - OG}You are talking about an instance\Nwhen a person ingests two fruits.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.54,0:22:37.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They die because their body\Ndisintegrates without a trace. - OG}The individual disintegrates\Nuntil nothing remains.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.71,0:22:40.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Greedy idiots bring ruin upon themselves. - OG}Greedy idiots cause their own downfall.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.80,0:22:43.43,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If they think about the risk that\Nthey carry with just one fruit, - OG}There's an inherent risk with just one fruit;{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.43,0:22:48.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{you'd think that they could guess how much of a curse the second one would bring them. - OG}they should've realized how the curse\Nmight amplify upon eating a second.{PP/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.68,0:22:51.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?! Is that so?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.85,0:22:56.52,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{In any case, I'm surprised that you were\Nable to obtain two devil fruits, Chief. - OG}{At any rate, Chief, it's crazy to think\Nyou managed to get even two devil fruits. - Z}But Chief, it's crazy to think you managed\Nto get your hands on {\i1}two{\i0} devil fruits.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.06,0:22:58.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Where on earth did you get them? - OG}Where'd you get them?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.23,0:23:01.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I have all sorts of connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.23,0:23:03.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Eat them to prepare for the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.78,0:23:07.45,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Become stronger, CP9! - OG}Become even stronger, CP9!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.45,0:23:09.95,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,{But let me tell you one thing. - OG}But I'll give you fair warning.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.95,0:23:13.96,Flashbacks-207+,,0,0,0,,I don't know what kinds of devils\Ndwell in those fruits.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.96,0:23:17.04,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's hard to believe that these\Nare fruits from this world. - OG}It's hard to believe these fruits\Nare of this world.{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.04,0:23:20.67,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I feel a mysterious power,\Nkind of like gravity, from them. - OG}{\q2}They give off what feels like a gravitational pull.{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.67,0:23:22.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{They're not listed in encyclopedias, either. - OG}Neither is listed in the reference books.{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.13,0:23:25.38,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,That seems to be how they normally are.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.38,0:23:29.80,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It's said that you can tell the name\Nof the fruit from the powers you gain, - OG}It's said you can infer the fruit's name\Nfrom the powers you exhibit,{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.80,0:23:32.81,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{but what kind of powers you'll gain is a gamble. - OG}but it's a crapshoot\Nas to what powers you gain.{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.18,0:23:37.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It'll be a terrible life if you gain\Nweird powers with this gamble. - OG}Your life takes a turn for the worse if you\Nobtain an offbeat power with this gamble.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.60,0:23:40.61,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{On top of that, to think that\Nyou'll become unable to swim... - OG}{What's more, to think that\Nyou can no longer swim... - Z}{Add losing the power to swim to that, and... - arch: making Gaijin happy}Add losing the ability to swim to that...{arch/Z- we can probably drop the "and" at the end to make this sound smoother, also changing "power" to "ability" to remove redundancy with the next line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.52,0:23:45.11,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No matter what powers they are,\Nit all depends on how you use them. - OG}No matter the power,\Nwhat counts is how it's used.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.11,0:23:47.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,In all likelihood, you won't become weaker.{OG+arch: OG is pretty literal and I can't find a better rewrite}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.78,0:23:50.91,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Being unable to swim is no drawback, either. - OG}Being unable to swim is\Nno big drawback, either.{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.91,0:23:57.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Countless sailors find death in their\Nquest for just one devil fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.50,0:24:01.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Go ahead and eat them.\NI'm curious to see what you'll become. - OG}Go ahead and eat them. Let's have some fun.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.34,0:24:05.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Kalifa, don't do it!\NNothing good will come of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.97,0:24:08.34,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It tastes like crap! Crap! - OG}It tastes like turds. Literal turds!{Gaijin}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.68,0:24:12.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Jabra doesn't want\NKaku and Kalifa to get stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.10,0:24:14.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's right! - OG}Such is the truth!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.60,0:24:20.65,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Your jealousy tarnishes your name. - OG}{Jealously tarnishes a man's good name. - Z}Jealously and envy tarnish a man's good name.{arch: he explicitly lists two synonyms}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.98,0:24:26.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Shut up, you jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.40,0:24:28.74,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two! Think about it carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.74,0:24:31.78,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Find the right buyer, and they'd be worth several hundred million belly! - OG}The right buyer will\Nnet you hundreds of millions,{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.78,0:24:34.70,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{One bite will ruin your life! - OG}but one bite will curse you for life!{Z}{but one bite could curse you for life! - arch}{Z - I'd opt for "will" because a devil fruit definitely curses someone}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.30,0:24:45.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That sounds interesting. - OG}Well, you've piqued my interest.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.84,0:24:49.09,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{If this is a winner, I'll welcome it. - OG}{If it means greater success, I welcome it. - Z}{If it holds a good power, I'll welcome it. - arch: this is very tough and no translation I checked has anything better. Lit. it's just "if it's a success" or "if I/we scored when picking this fruit".}If this fruit's a winner, I'll welcome it.{PP/Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.34,0:24:53.64,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,They ate them, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.19,0:25:03.19,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.19,0:25:10.41,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Have you noticed any changes in your body?! - OG}Have you noticed any physical changes?!{PJ}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.92,0:25:21.83,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– It's disgusting.\N– It's disgusting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.83,0:25:23.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Couldn't you have said that sooner?! - OG}Say that sooner!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.33,0:25:24.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{It tastes terrible!! - OG}{It's disgusting! - Z}It tastes awful!{arch: shouldn't be the same as 6:21, the japanese is different and more formal}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.59,0:25:26.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We've already heard that! - OG}You already said that!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.21,0:25:29.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't say that after you ate the whole thing! - OG}You should say that {\i1}before{\i0}\Nconsuming the whole thing!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.26,0:25:35.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, try doing something!\NWhat kind of powers did you get?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.85,0:25:39.60,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I don't feel like anything changed. - OG}I don't feel like anything is different.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.60,0:25:42.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{You'll soon notice\Nhow big the change is. - OG}You'll soon notice the enormity of the change.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.48,0:25:46.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is the birth of new devil fruit users. - OG}{This is the birth of new powers. - Gaijin}You've been reborn with new abilities.{Z/PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.90,0:25:48.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I look forward to seeing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.49,0:25:52.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Get a handle on your own powers at least, while you have a chance. - OG}{At the very least, get a handle\Non your new abilities during this down time. - Z}At the very least, get a handle\Non your abilities during this downtime.{Evo: bracketed "new" to avoid repetition, I feel like that part is clear either way. Removed space from downtime}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.91,0:25:57.33,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\c&H000000&\t(0,267,1,\c&HFFFFFF&)}{Depending on the chief's command,\Nyou may be able to try them in a real battle immediately... - OG}Depending on the chief's orders,\Nthey might get an early field test.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.95,0:26:03.46,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{though it seems that Blueno couldn't wait,\Nand joined the festivities before us. - OG}although Blueno did get impatient\Nand joined the festivities before us.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.89,0:26:15.01,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.89,0:26:21.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.10,0:26:23.85,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Oimo and Kashi are back in action!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.85,0:26:25.36,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{This is bad.... - OG}Of all the rotten...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.36,0:26:29.94,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We don't have the energy to fight guys like them. - OG}{We don't have the energy\Nfor another fight with these... - arch: Ellipsis since he also trails off in Japanese.}We don't have the energy\Nfor another fight with them...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.03,0:26:34.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Is this it for us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.70,0:26:40.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hurry up and stomp on them! - OG}{Hurry over here and stomp on them! - Z}Hurry over here and stomp them to pieces!{arch: "stomp on them" feels... to specific, and omits the actual intention. Lit. it's "crush them by stomping on them", or something like "stomp them into the ground".}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.12,0:26:42.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Take care of those three, giants! - OG}Take these three out, you giants!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.92,0:26:53.63,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,How...{Used as flashback in Enies Lobby 23 @timestamp 05:02}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.63,0:26:56.05,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,...dare you...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.51,0:27:00.97,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Huh?\N– Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.97,0:27:02.98,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– ...deceive us?!\N– ...deceive us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.07,0:27:12.40,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wh-What the hell?! Those two\Nwent over to the enemy's side!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.07,0:27:15.82,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Before we rejoice\Nover the safety of our chiefs... - OG}Before we rejoice\Nover the safety of our chiefs...{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.82,0:27:18.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,before we grieve over our wasted years...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.32,0:27:22.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{We'll take out all our anger on\Nthese guys in a furious rampage! - OG}{We'll expend all our anger on these cowards\Nin a fierce rampage! -Z}We'll let loose our rage\Nupon these deceitful cowards!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.83,0:27:26.21,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Let's go together... King of Snipers!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.84,0:27:35.26,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{No need for formalities! - OG}I strongly concur!{arch: Or "I do concur!" or some other fancy way to say "I agree"}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.26,0:27:37.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Raise the counterattack signal this time for sure! - OG}The time has come to signal the counterstrike!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.84,0:27:40.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Hurry, to our comrades in arms! - OG}Hurry, to our brothers-in-arms!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.07,0:27:54.69,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I underestimated you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.07,0:27:57.16,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Don't! - OG}Well, don't!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.16,0:28:00.70,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{I never thought that he'd keep\Nup with the speed of Shave. - OG}I never thought he would\Nkeep pace with shave.{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.70,0:28:02.20,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,I should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.04,0:28:05.62,Thoughts-207+,,0,0,0,,{Since he's a rubber man,\Nhitting him wouldn't work, right? - OG}Hitting a rubber man will be ineffective, right?{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.62,0:28:06.87,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Moon Walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.46,0:28:10.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Gum-Gum...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.96,0:28:11.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Tempest Kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.97,0:28:19.14,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Iron Body!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.18,0:28:22.18,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Wheel!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.57,0:28:33.90,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Door Door!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.28,0:28:40.53,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{A-A door just opened on the ground! - OG}Huh? A-A door opened on the ground!{Evo}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.53,0:28:41.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Door Door.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.91,0:28:46.45,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wh-What the heck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.45,0:28:49.00,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Were there small doors here?! - OG}Were these small doors here before?!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.00,0:28:54.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,C-C-Crap! I got stuck! Dammit! These things...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.30,0:28:57.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,You! What's this?! What'd you do?!\NIs this a devil fruit power?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.88,0:29:00.39,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I'm a door human\Nwith Door-Door devil fruit powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.76,0:29:04.10,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I can turn anything into a door!{OG}{lit. it's "I can turn any separating thing into a door". But this makes so little sense in English that I'd leave it. -arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.56,0:29:09.06,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Revolving Door.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.98,0:29:14.23,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,What?! What?! Wh-What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.23,0:29:15.73,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{I feel dizzy! - OG}{I'm getting dizzy! - Z}Everything's spinning!{arch: there's kind of a pun here where he uses a word for "dizzy" that literally means "my eyes are spinning". Between keeping "dizzy" and keeping the pun, I'd go for the pun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.99,0:29:20.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Wh-Wh-Which way is forward?! Stop! - OG}Wh-Wh-Which way is forward?! Make it stop!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.20,0:29:21.32,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)}Tempest Kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.79,0:29:33.08,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hey, cook!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.08,0:29:34.79,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.79,0:29:37.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Luffy's already fighting CP9.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.96,0:29:38.92,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– What?!\N– What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.92,0:29:40.59,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,I-Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.59,0:29:42.30,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Dammit! We got off to a late start!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.93,0:29:46.93,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,But how do we break out\Nof this encirclement?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.93,0:29:50.31,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Someone hit Gomorrah with a flail,\Nand now he can't move! - OG}{Gomorrah took all these flail hits\Nand can't move anymore! - arch: JP doesn't specify if singular or plural, and plural both makes more sense and fits earlier in the episode.}Gomorrah took all these flail hits,\Nand now he can't move!{Z- sounds good, but changing the the second part to the OG since it looks cleaner as a cause and effect.}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.31,0:29:54.56,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Fire! Shoot those pirates\Ndown from that beast! - OG}Fire! Shoot those pirates off that beast!{arch}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.32,0:30:00.28,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,There's only one way out!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.70,0:30:03.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're gonna make\Na dash for the courthouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.91,0:30:05.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{That's the only choice we have. - OG}{Looks like we have to. - arch: OG seemed too literal, but open for other suggestions in this spirit.}Looks like we'll have to.{Z- previous line had "gonna" so we can keep this in future tense.}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.20,0:30:09.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{All right, let's go, guys! - OG}All right, let's go, boys!{PP}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.66,0:30:10.75,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,– Yeah!\N– Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.75,0:30:11.96,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.37,0:30:14.88,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Nobody get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.59,0:30:16.50,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Chopper?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.01,0:30:23.51,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Hold on tight!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.28,0:30:40.86,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Gomorrah...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.86,0:30:43.49,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Gomorrah says so!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.86,0:30:45.20,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Th-The monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.20,0:30:46.66,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,...is still alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.66,0:30:49.37,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Fire! Use the RPGs to take it down! - OG}Fire! Use your rockets to take it down!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.37,0:30:51.12,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Shoot the monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.12,0:30:53.71,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,{Fight back! Back up Gomorrah! - OG}Fight back! Protect Gomorrah!{Z}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.51,0:31:04.84,Main-207+,,0,0,0,,Go! Gomorrah!
